65. tunicato: the cumbrous toga was seldom wom by the poorer classes at Rome, except on ceremonial occasions. Tac. Dial. 7 volgus imperitum et tunicalus hic populus. Augustus was annoyed at the disuse of the national dress, and forbade the citizens to appear in the foxum or circus without the toga (Suet. Aug. 40).
